Title: record label
Description: brand and trademark associated with the marketing of subject music recordings and music videos

Title: field of work
Description: fields of work related to this item (physics, history) . For occupation like physicist, historian see P106. Note: Can be used in any item besides person

Title: position held
Description: subject currently or formerly holds the object position or public office

Title: original network
Description: network(s) the radio or television show was originally aired on. This does not include later re-runs or additional syndication.

Title: genre
Description: genre of a creative work or genre in which an artist works

Title: instrument
Description: instrument that a person plays

Title: occupation
Description: occupation of a person; see also "field of work" (Property:P101)

Title: language
Description: language of a work (not necessarily original language, use P364 instead or as well)

Title: named after
Description: entity or event that inspired the subject's name, or namesake (in at least one language)

Title: original language
Description: language in which a work was originally created

Title: position played on team
Description: position the player plays, e.g. Small Forward

Title: continent
Description: continent of which the subject is a part. Use for countries, locations in Antarctica and items located in such areas, that are located in more than one continent.

Title: manufacturer
Description: main manufacturer of this product (excluding sub-contracted manufacturers)

Title: country of origin
Description: country of origin of the creative work or subject item

Title: sport
Description: sport or discipline in which the entity participates or belongs to

Title: headquarters location
Description: specific location where an organization's HQ is or has been situated

Title: formation location
Description: location where a group or organization was formed

Title: languages spoken
Description: language(s) that a person speaks. Primarily used to indicate non-native languages

Title: located in
Description: location the physical object or event is within

Title: official language
Description: language designated as official by this item

Title: owned by
Description: owner of the subject

Title: place of death
Description: the most specific known (e.g. city instead of country)

Title: place of birth
Description: the most specific known (e.g. city instead of country)

Title: shares border with
Description: countries or administrative subdivisions, of equal level, that this item borders, either by land or water

Title: work location
Description: location(s) where the creator was active

Title: employer
Description: organization for which the subject works or worked

Title: is in the administrative territorial entity
Description: the item is located on the territory of the following administrative entity

Title: native language
Description: language that a person learned natively

Title: country
Description: sovereign state of this item

Title: developer
Description: organisation or person that developed this item

Title: capital of
Description: country, state, department, canton or other administrative division of which the municipality is the governmental seat

Title: capital
Description: location (city, municipality) of governmental seat of the country, or administrative territorial entity
